<paragraph id="8400A579FFD0FF9FDEB8F83EFD89FEEC" blockId="5.[136,1452,1920,2091]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,364]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="89" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD0FF9CDEB8F83EFF71F81A" bold="true" box="[189,245,1920,1946]" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Note</emphasis>
:—This species can be distinguished by its compact pseudisidia and the presence of stictic acid as the only metabolite. 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD0FF9CDF09F81AFC34F83E" authority="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha (2011: 314)" authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha" authorityPageNumber="314" authorityYear="2011" box="[268,944,1956,1983]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sticticum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD0FF9CDF09F81AFD8AF83E" box="[268,526,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">Herpothallon sticticum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E02ED888FFD0FF9CDC10F81AFC34F83E" author="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M. &amp; Sinha, P. G." box="[533,944,1956,1983]" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" pagination="313 - 316" refId="ref3884" refString="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M. &amp; Sinha, P. G. (2011) A new species and a new record of Herpothallon (lichenized Ascomycota) from India. Mycotaxon 116: 313 - 316. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 116.313" type="journal article" year="2011">Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha (2011: 314)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD0FF9CDDBEF81BFF3EF863" authority="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha (2009: 611)" authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha" authorityPageNumber="611" authorityYear="2009" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="isidiatum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD0FF9CDDBEF81BFBC1F83E" box="[955,1093,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">H. isidiatum</emphasis>
Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha (2009: 611)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD0FF9CDF02F877FDE1F862" authority="G. Thor (2009: 39)" authorityName="G. Thor" authorityPageNumber="39" authorityYear="2009" box="[263,613,1992,2018]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD0FF9CDF02F877FE05F862" box="[263,385,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">H. elegans</emphasis>
G. Thor (2009: 39)
</taxonomicName>
also contain stictic acid, but 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD0FF9CDDB2F877FBC5F862" authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha" authorityYear="2011" box="[951,1089,1993,2018]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sticticum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD0FF9CDDB2F877FBC5F862" box="[951,1089,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">H. sticticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a grey to pale yellow–grey thallus and dense, minutely felty, granular globular to short cylindrical 0.05–0.1(–0.25) × 0.05–0.1(–0.2) mm wide pseudisidia with projecting hyphae (
<bibRefCitation id="E02ED888FFD0FF9CDC2DF7AEFCCDF7AA" author="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M. &amp; Sinha, P. G." box="[552,841,2064,2090]" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" pagination="313 - 316" refId="ref3884" refString="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M. &amp; Sinha, P. G. (2011) A new species and a new record of Herpothallon (lichenized Ascomycota) from India. Mycotaxon 116: 313 - 316. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 116.313" type="journal article" year="2011">Jagadeesh &amp; Sinha 2011</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD0FF9CDD65F7AFFC69F7AA" authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha" authorityYear="2009" box="[864,1005,2064,2090]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="isidiatum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD0FF9CDD65F7AFFC69F7AA" box="[864,1005,2064,2090]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="88">H. isidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a grey to whitish grey thallus and larger pseudisidia (0.08–0.15 × 
<quantity id="4347089CFFD3FF9FDFE9FF20FDF7FF39" box="[492,627,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 mm</quantity>
) with dark brown to black pycnidia at the tips (Jagadeesh &amp; Sinha 2009); 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD3FF9FDE8DFF7DFE84FF5C" authorityName="G. Thor" authorityYear="2009" box="[136,256,194,220]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDE8DFF7DFE84FF5C" box="[136,256,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a hypothallus with a red layer (partly absent) and with a smooth and black layer and dark red prothallus beneath that (
<bibRefCitation id="E02ED888FFD3FF9FDF1EFF58FE76FE80" author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Thor, G. &amp; Lucking, R. &amp; Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L." box="[283,498,230,256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" pagination="19 - 66" refId="ref3477" refString="Aptroot, A., Thor, G., Lucking, R., Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L. (2009) The lichen genus Herpothallon reinstated. Bibliotheca Lichenologica 99: 19 - 66. [http: // www. nhm 2. uio. no / botanisk / lav / RLL / PDF / R 30504. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2009">
Aptroot 
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDF7CFF59FE34FE80" box="[377,432,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). This species can also be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD3FF9FDDAAFF59FE30FEA4" authority="(Vain.) Nelsen, Lucking &amp; Rivas Plata (2012: 318)" authorityName="Nelsen, Lucking &amp; Rivas Plata" authorityPageNumber="318" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Vain." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Diorygma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="antillarum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDDAAFF59FB18FE80" box="[943,1180,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Diorygma antillarum</emphasis>
(Vain.) Nelsen, Lücking &amp; Rivas Plata (2012: 318)
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD3FF9FDFDBFEB5FDD4FEA4" box="[478,592,267,292]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Diorygma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDFDBFEB5FDD4FEA4" box="[478,592,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Diorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hypothallus is compact, not byssoid, and pseudisidia are unknown with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD3FF9FDF46FE91FE5FFEC8" authorityName="Nelsen, Lucking &amp; Rivas Plata" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Vain." box="[323,475,302,328]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Diorygma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="antillarum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDF46FE91FE5FFEC8" box="[323,475,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">D. antillarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has a distinct carbonized hypothallus, but contains different substances from 
<taxonomicName id="43BFDEFAFFD3FF9FDB95FE91FD8DFEEC" authority="(Nelsen et al. 2012)" baseAuthorityName="Nelsen" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="polyisidiatum">
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDB95FE91FEA4FEEC" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. polyisidiatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E02ED888FFD3FF9FDF2AFEECFD86FEEC" author="Nelsen, P. M. &amp; Lucking, R. &amp; Andrew, C. J. &amp; Rivas-Plata, E. &amp; Chaves, J. L. &amp; Caceres, M. E. S. &amp; Ventura, N." box="[303,514,338,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" pagination="313 - 321" refId="ref4043" refString="Nelsen, P. M., Lucking, R., Andrew, C. J., Rivas-Plata, E., Chaves, J. L., Caceres, M. E. S. &amp; Ventura, N. (2012) Dismantling Herpothallon: Herpothallon antillarum (Arthoniomycetes: Arthoniaceae) is a member of the genus Diorygma (Lecanoromycetes: Graphidaceae). The Bryologist 115: 313 - 321. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1639 / 0007 - 2745 - 115.2.313" type="journal article" year="2012">
Nelsen 
<emphasis id="B6CB796BFFD3FF9FDF83FEEDFE3AFEEC" box="[390,446,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
